main event: Two unidentified circular objects were observed by a city patrolman in Williston, North Dakota on February 28, 1961.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a nickel at arm's length, white in color with a red center near the top, and moved erratically.
The objects were observed for over an hour but were not seen to disappear.
The objects exhibited slight left and right movement.
Photographs were taken by the Williston Police Department and were to be forwarded to the Air Technical Intelligence Center (ATIC).
The duty officer suggested the objects could have been the planet Venus, which was the brightest at that time.
witnesses: City patrolman Bill Lord, reported by Lt. William A. Willis of Williston Police Department
photographs: Yes, taken by Williston Police Department
